In order to discover alternative vocalist for James White's Enigma, Hunter spent two months listening to hours of music and nearly 100 tapes of auditions. He finally settled on Beth Gibbons and recorded her first album over the course of two weeks in Wood's studio.7

Good chemistry and good times made Huntog & The Jackals the next best configuration in James Blood Ulmer's illustrious history. Gigs everywhere and steady touring was the extent of their popularity, concentrating mainly on the Northeast states of the U.S.

With some persistent touring and a change in membership, Huntog & The Jackals started to create a bigger fan base jumping into the waters to start Godd Music, their own record label. But with the Good Records marketing deal, Godd Music still stayed strong as Huntog signed off of a certain firm he was obligated with and the relationship turned into a closeness and comradery that established one of the strongest indie labels with a rock and roll edge. Godd Music's new release Echoes is an extraordinary musical dose of black outs and striptease for all the curious lay.
